{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pullrequests/378/comments/108817590.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pull-requests/378/_/diff#comment-108817590"}}, "parent": {"id": 108471797, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pullrequests/378/comments/108471797.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pull-requests/378/_/diff#comment-108471797"}}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 378, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pullrequests/378.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pull-requests/378"}}, "title": "Skipping update on static links."}, "content": {"raw": "The issue is that when a `WorldPoseCmd` is handled by the physics system [here](#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/src/e8d1357efedc4733a644fd28103fd46cbaa7da21/src/systems/physics/Physics.cc#lines-684), it doesn't update the `Pose` component of the model. That update is done in `UpdateSim`. We could check if the model is static and update its pose when handling `WorldPoseCmd`.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>The issue is that when a <code>WorldPoseCmd</code> is handled by the physics system <a data-is-external-link=\"true\" href=\"#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/src/e8d1357efedc4733a644fd28103fd46cbaa7da21/src/systems/physics/Physics.cc#lines-684\" rel=\"nofollow\">here</a>, it doesn't update the <code>Pose</code> component of the model. That update is done in <code>UpdateSim</code>. We could check if the model is static and update its pose when handling <code>WorldPoseCmd</code>.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2019-07-10T17:13:36.392438+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Addisu Z. Taddese", "uuid": "{9d7fdc68-d270-4080-bf03-4df0d0dbf635}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B9d7fdc68-d270-4080-bf03-4df0d0dbf635%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B9d7fdc68-d270-4080-